{"accepted":[{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Surpassed some past constructions.","id":"vf_4f2692eaa118d9a3","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #507: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $\\alpha(n)$ be such that every set of $n$ points in the unit disk contains three points which determine a triangle of area at most $\\alpha(n)$. Estimate $\\alpha(n)$. Current best: The current best bounds are\\[\\frac{\\log n}{n^2}\\ll \\alpha(n) \\ll \\frac{1}{n^{7/6+o(1)}}.\\]The lower bound is due to Koml\\'{o}s, Pintz, and Szemer\\'{e}di \\cite{KPS82}. The upper bound is due to Cohen, Pohoata, and Zakharov \\cite{CPZ24} (improving on their earlier work \\cite{CPZ23} which itself improves an exponent of $8/7$ due to Koml\\'{o}s, Pintz, and Szemer\\'{e}di \\cite{KPS81}). and Zakharov, D., A new upper bound for the Heilbronn triangle problem. [KPS82] Koml\\'{o}s, J\\'{a}nos and Pintz, J\\'{a}nos and Szemer\\'{e}di, Endre, A lower bound for Heilbronn's problem. Prize: no. Tags: geometry.","id":"vf_69ddffd09cfcc588","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos507.erdos_507.upper https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos507.erdos_507.upper.","id":"vf_849eab3f6adf9c17","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/507.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_4f2692eaa118d9a3","source_root":"sha256:1faedc24f040a60a22177b456c74b969a61ce8836082297b1835797a57b4fa56","target":"erdos:507","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_69ddffd09cfcc588","source